<section id="stakes" class="py-[var(--spacing-section)] border-t border-slate-gray">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-3xl" data-animate="headline">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white mb-8" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Here's what most muralists and sign shops won't tell you.
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-6" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
      <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        They don't ask questions. They show up, look at the wall, and start painting whatever they were going to paint anyway. Or they take your logo, print it on vinyl, and stick it to your wall before they move on to the next job. The work looks fine. Nobody stops for it. Nobody remembers it. Nobody walks into your business because of it.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
        That is what happens when nobody thinks about what the work should be about before they start.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
